what tips would you give an aspiring writefag who hasn't written anything yet but a very simple greentext that was kinda shitposty?
Anonymous
  • Post
  • Report

Anonymous Fri 15 Mar 2019 06:40:09 No.21897734 Report
Quoted By: >>21897854 >>21897959
>>21897642
Set goals for yourself and try to write every day, even if it's only fifty words so you get into the habit of doing things regularly. Also planning is really important, outline your general plot and what you want to cover in each chapter so when you're not staring at the document wondering where you should start.

Decide if you want to write in first person, second person or third person and stick with it. Make sure to run your first draft through an editing website to screen for easy errors to fix. Do you have a prompt or general idea of what you want to write? Hopefully this advice helps you out some even though everything might not apply to you.
